                     <title xml:lang="en" key="work_8716">Addresses to Major Robert Garstin</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar"/>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar" defective="true"/>
                     <note>Addresses to <persName xml:lang="en" type="supplied" key="person_f2089" role="rcp" change="#role-assignment">Major Robert Garstin</persName>, of the Madras Army, Government Agent at Chepauk, from <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f2868" role="aut" change="#role-assignment">Muḥammad Ṣalābat Khān Naṣīr al-Mulk Intiẓām al-Dawlah Ghazanfar Jang Bahādur, <foreign xml:lang="fa">محمد صلابت خان نصیر الملک انتظام الدوله</foreign>
                        </persName> dated <date calendar="Hijri-qamari" when="1847">25 Zuʼl-H. 1263</date> (see <ref target=" Uk_IO_Islamic_4794">I. O. Islamic 4794</ref>), and from <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f3399" role="aut" change="#role-assignment">Qiyām al-Dawlah Bahādur, <foreign xml:lang="fa">قیام الدوله بهادر</foreign>
                        </persName>, and <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f3360" role="aut" change="#role-assignment">Qamar al-Dawlah Bahādur <foreign xml:lang="fa">قمر الدوله بهادر</foreign>
                        </persName> dated <date calendar="Gregorian" when="1847">1 Jan. 1847</date>
                     </note>
                     <note>Also includes a verse written in his honour by <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f2499" role="ctb" change="#role-assignment">Muḥammad Badr al-Dīn Ḥusayn Khān <foreign xml:lang="fa">محمد بدر الدین حسین خان</foreign>
                        </persName> dated <date calendar="Gregorian" when="1849">1849</date> and an undated copy of it
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>For a more detailed description see Sims-Williams 1986, page 21.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="en">Persian and English</textLang>
                     <note/>
